envious /ˈɛnvɪəs/

1. ADJ If you are envious of someone, you want something that they have. 羡慕的 

例： I don't think I'm envious of your success. 我不认为我羡慕你的成功。 

例： Do I sound envious? I pity them, actually. 我听起来像是羡慕吗？其实，我可怜他们。 

2. enviously ADV 羡慕地 [ADV with v] 

例： 'You haven't changed,' I am often enviously told. “你没变，”我常被羡慕地告知。

